Multivariate Plots and Analysis

First of all come again with the strong relation we have: quality vs alcohol. In this case we add sulphates feature in order to see if increases the correlation.

Here you can see the plot:

## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess'

You can see thereâs no apparent relation for sulphates. Only can observe thereâs extreme low sulphates rate on better and on poor wines. I suspect high quality wines thereâs no sulphates because of they think on better quality rates and in lower quality wines because they want not to spent so much in order to have affordable bottles.

Also we can see removing outliers in Sulphates feature maybe we would have a more clear correlation.

We can do something similar but taking in density feature instead sulphates:

## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess'

You can see thereâs a relation between density and quality. All of the High Class Wines have low density rate. There is not so strong relation as alcohol but thinking on a future prediction model (for example) is sure itâs a feature to include.
